well, and warrior too now, I suppose.<br>
<br>
To go over the skills:<br>
<br>
Acrobatics: (3 skill levels) - Yay! I get to pay massive amounts of xp (total of what? 18 points?) for something that monks get for free: uber safe fall skill. Foff.<br>
<br>
Adv. Trap Negotiation: (3 skill levels) - Oh happy happy joy joy. The most inane ability of the rogue in EQ, and arguably the most boring (I just love sitting on traps, disarming them every 20 seconds).  This skill is worse than useless, since you can already disarm traps faster than they become active again.<br>
<br>
Ambidexterity: (1 skill level - cost 9 skill points) - I already hit 90-95% dual wield rolls. Nuff said.<br>
<br>
Chaotic Stab: (1 skill level - cost 6 skill points) - Nearly a saving grace, but... about as roguely as a twohanded sword.  Should have allowed a greater flanking area for normal backstab.  Instead of being able to only get stabs on the back 120 degrees, that should have been upped to the back 240 degrees, to include flank attacks in backstabs.<br>
<br>
Double Riposte: (3 skill levels) - HAHAHAHHAHAHA.  Foff.<br>
<br>
Escape: (1 skill level - cost 9 skill points) - wow. once every 72 minutes? Can you shaft me harder? Is it worth even having a hotkey up for this skill?<br>
<br>
Poison Mastery: (3 skill levels) - Might have been useful. If poisons were stackable.  If they didn't require farming rare components off of greens, or worse, harm touching greens (yay scorpkis venom).<br>
<br>
Purge Poison: (1 skill level - cost 5 skill points) - oh @#%$. another once-every-72-minutes skill.  I'm not a f~ing paladin or SK.  What's with this once every game day crap?  What? would I abuse this skill on... trakanon? pfft.<br>
<br>
Personally, i'd rather boost stats than bother getting most of this crap.  And we all know how worthless stats are. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhippophobiccowboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippophobic Cowboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/19/01 1:04:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=86>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Alternate Advancement</span><hr size=1> Guys, dont worry, go over to a monk forum and you'll find they're none too happy with their new skills either. But I agree, skills like double riposte seem absolutely superficial. I think they should have not bothered putting skills like that in - it seems like they were desperate to fill space.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeltarinstormshadow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keltarin Stormshadow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/19/01 2:00:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=87>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Alternate Advancement</span><hr size=1> Has anybody tried double-riposte with the counterattack discipline?  Seems to me that's the obvious thing to use it with (though it didn't hit me till just now).<br>
