Slinker <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=plaigan>Plaigan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/19/01 6:34:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=90>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Alternate Advancement</span><hr size=1> Since everyone is complaining about the new skills I figure I may as well put in my two cents about what should have been.  These are actually complaints I had a long time ago that everyone told me to STFU about but maybe you guys will be more receptive.<br>
<br>
Just because they are melee archetype's doesn't mean they should effect all melee classes identically.  Finishing Blow is a toy for Monks and less useful for Rogues.  It would become drastically more useful if it raised the maximum level for a mob that can be assassinated (presuming they are under a % of hp) along with raising the standard assassinate percentage.  Same basic principle can be applied to the monk's abilities.  It would help with soloing drastically if assassinate would work on an ID'd 55 that was running with 50% of it's hp.  First skill level you can Assassinate sub 50% mobs up to 48, second skill level is up to 51, final is up to 55.<br>
<br>
Get rid of Adv. Trap Negotiation all together, traps never really did work.  Replace the skill with one that allows a rogue to slow a mob's movement, before you think it's a bad idea lemme explain the context.  You take a throwing dagger, aim at the Achille's Tendon of an enemy and throw, presuming the dagger hits the tendon is severed and the mob moves much slower.  So it would be a percentage increasing up to 10% on every landed throw that was issued from behind a mob, the code is already there for determining whether a projectile was thrown behind a mob (remember assassinate on thrown weapons?) so it would be a pretty easy one to code and it would help solo'ing a bit.  Poking an ID'd slow moving mob.  Of course there would have to be a check to see if the mob is susceptible to such attacks (it wouldn't be that realistic if you tried it on a beholder now would it?)  More useful than Adv. Trap Negotiation if you ask me.<br>
<br>
Chaotic Stab is actually pretty realistic when you think about it although poorly named.  Fighting a guard and stabbing your Ragebringer through their side and puncturing a lung is quite possible.  VI should add 2 more skill levels if you ask me though.  75% chance at the second level to do up to 1/4 maximum backstab damage.  50% chance at the third level to do up to 1/2 maximum backstab damage.  If it fails the 75/100 or 50/100 check (respectively) it still does minimum backstab damage.  More roguely if you ask me.  I always really thought backstab should do some damage from the front, of course it would be more of a sidestab but that's just semantics.<br>
<br>
Escape could be much more helpful if they changed it from 1 to 5 skill levels, first skill level 72 minute refresh, second skill level 36 minute refresh, third skill level 18 minute refresh, fourth skill level 9 minute refresh, fifth skill level 4 1/2 minute refresh.  The amount of time spent hunting for the skill points required is immense but it improves a skill.  The only problem is that with this skill a less honorable rogue could use it to train people, that's really the only reason I can see that VI wouldn't implement it.  Of course Necro's, SK's, and Monk's get actually the same skill with a far less refresh time at a much lower cost.  I would like to see Escape.<br>
<br>
Acrobatics should cost barely anything to raise your skill level in.  Nine points for a third level is idiotic.  If the skill point requirement was lowered it would actually be a good ability.<br>
<br>
Ambidexterity is a crock. But real ambidexterous people are equally skilled and equally strong in both arms.  Strength modifier for off hand damage, not as high as primary though, would be my solution to an utterly useless skill.<br>
<br>
Purge Poison makes no sense, it's really pretty stupid considering that Rogues are a melee class.  If VI really wanted to give us a purge poison ability they should grant us the ability to make a potion that will purge all poisons from our body, not an ability that does it.  Get rid of Purge Poison and give us what I always wanted, a &quot;Deft Hands&quot; skill.  Three levels, first level increases the mob level that can be pick pocketed to 50, second to 55, third to 60.  At the third level you also get the ability to pick pocket magic items (incidentally allowing you to disarm magic weapons as well).  Of course I can hear every other class over every server complaining &quot;A rogue just stole from the MOB I was killing.&quot;  For that the solution is a secondary item pool only accessable by pick pocket.  Now before anyone jumps on my back because of the fact this would increase item influx they have to realize that the odds of pickpocketing anything off of a level 60 mob is VERY VERY difficult, if everyone remembers from their youth how lower level mobs were easier to steal from than higher level mobs they'll realize how hard it will be to steal from higher level mobs.  The second loot pool would have to be generated independantly from the first.  Rogues always had hordes of loot and were the richest of all classes, with this skill we could reclaim the title of richest.<br>
<br>
I await the flames of my peers.<br>
<br>
-Plaigan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uslinkerdread.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SlinkerDread</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/19/01 7:19:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=91>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Alternate Advancement</span><hr size=1> plaigan did u read my input then decide to post? lol you quote some exact opinions I posted 3 hours earlier.<br>
